zy-load.jpg 1304w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"mt-6\">After setting option toggle, you will see how it works.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full screen-capture\"><img width=\"930\" height=\"441\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/lazy-1.jpg\" alt=\"Feature Image\" class=\"wp-image-1999\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/lazy-1.jpg 930w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/lazy-1-300x142.jpg 300w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/lazy-1-768x364.jpg 768w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/lazy-1-150x71.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"mt-9\">Where is Lazy Load Enabled?<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"mb-0\">Lazy load in enabled in all pages and elements in UDesign.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:60%\">\n<ul><li>Blog Grid with multi-columns<\/li><li>Blog Masonry &#8211; 2 Columns, 3Columns, 4 Columns<\/li><li>Blog Mask &#8211; Grid, Masonry<\/li><li>Banner Element<\/li><li>Product Archive<\/li><li>Product Categories Element<\/li><li>Portfolio Archive<\/li><\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:40%\">\n<ul><li>Image Box Element<\/li><li>Products Element<\/li><li>Banner + Products Element<\/li><li>Single Product Element<\/li><li>Single Portfolio Element<\/li><li>Single Member Element<\/li><\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Here, we discussed Image lazy loading. What this does is to only load the images that are visible in the viewport. As the user scrolls and more images come into vi